## Architecture Summary

### Two-Level Context

```
StepperContext
  value: string              // currently active step value
  onValueChange: fn          // called when a step is selected
  orientation: "horizontal" | "vertical"

  └── StepperItemContext (one per StepperItem)
        value: string        // this item's own value
        isActive: boolean    // value === StepperContext.value
        disabled: boolean    // passed as prop to StepperItem
```

### Component Responsibility Matrix

| Component | Reads from | Renders as | Key behavior |
|-----------|-----------|------------|--------------|
| `Stepper` | — | `<div>` | Owns state, provides `StepperContext` |
| `StepperItem` | `StepperContext` | `<div>` | Provides `StepperItemContext`, sets `data-active` |
| `StepperTrigger` | Both contexts | `<button>` | Calls `onValueChange` on click, handles disabled |
| `StepperTitle` | — | `<p>` | Pure presentational wrapper |
| `StepperDescription` | — | `<p>` | Pure presentational wrapper |
| `StepperSeparator` | `StepperContext` | `<div>` | Changes CSS based on orientation |
| `StepperContent` | `StepperContext` | `<div>` or `null` | Renders only when `value === activeValue` |

### Horizontal Layout (user-authored structure in examples)

```
<Stepper orientation="horizontal">
  <div class="flex flex-row items-center">   ← user-authored flex row
    <StepperItem value="a">
      <StepperTrigger>...</StepperTrigger>
    </StepperItem>
    <StepperSeparator />                     ← h-px flex-1 bg-border
    <StepperItem value="b">
      <StepperTrigger>...</StepperTrigger>
    </StepperItem>
    <StepperSeparator />
    <StepperItem value="c">
      <StepperTrigger>...</StepperTrigger>
    </StepperItem>
  </div>
  <StepperContent value="a">...</StepperContent>
  <StepperContent value="b">...</StepperContent>
  <StepperContent value="c">...</StepperContent>
</Stepper>
```

### Vertical Layout (user-authored structure in examples)

```
<Stepper orientation="vertical">
  <StepperItem value="a">          ← flex flex-row gap-4
    <div class="flex flex-col">
      <StepperTrigger>
        <span>1</span>             ← user-rendered indicator
        <div>
          <StepperTitle />
          <StepperDescription />
        </div>
      </StepperTrigger>
      <StepperContent value="a" class="ms-12">
        ...
      </StepperContent>
    </div>
    <StepperSeparator />           ← ms-4 w-px self-stretch bg-border
  </StepperItem>
  ...
</Stepper>
```

Note: In the vertical layout, `StepperSeparator` inside `StepperItem` (which is `flex-row`) creates the vertical line to the left of the content area. The `ms-4` aligns it with the center of a typical 32px (size-8) step indicator when the indicator sits at the left edge.

